HEADWORD: Infraction
<hw>In*frac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infractio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>infraction</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act
of infracting or breaking; breach; violation; nonobservance;
infringement; <as>as, an <ex>infraction</ex> of a treaty, compact, rule,
or law</as>.</def> <rj><au>I. Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

